# Game/Replay/AnimateMoveStack.elm — EARLY

Replay animation driver for the MoveStack primitive — a stack
is dragged to an open board location without merging with
anything. Companion to `AnimateSplit` and `AnimateMergeStack`;
one of three synchronous board-drag animators extracted from
the former `prepareReplayStep` in 2026-04-22's
REFACTOR_ELM_REPLAY B1/Axis X.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Shape identical to its sibling Animate
  modules; see `AnimateSplit.claude` for the naming
  rationale.

## Interface

```elm
start :
    { stack : CardStack, newLoc : BoardLocation }
    -> List State.GesturePoint
    -> PathFrame
    -> Model
    -> Float
    -> Maybe Space.AnimationInfo
```

## Dependencies

- `Game.Replay.Space` — for `boardStackSource` and
  `AnimationInfo`.
- `Game.CardStack` — for `BoardLocation`.
- `Game.WireAction` — for `WA.MoveStack`.
- `Main.State` — for `Model`, `PathFrame`, `GesturePoint`.

## Pointers

- Called from `Game.Replay.Time.startBoardAnim`'s
  `WA.MoveStack payload ->` branch.
- Companion modules: `AnimateMergeStack`.
